name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t produce a charge on its own.

attack.name: Splashing Dodge
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Galvantula

abilities.name: Compound Eyes
abilities.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon do 50 more damage to your opponent’s Active Pokémon that has an Ability (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

attack.name: Shocking Web
attack.text: If this Pokémon has any Lightning Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Rowlet
flavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.

attack.name: Add On
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Dartrix
flavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

attack.name: United Wings
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile that has the United Wings attack.

name: Decidueye
flavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye’s shots never miss.

attack.name: Stock Up on Feathers
attack.text: Draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

attack.name: Power Shot
attack.text: Discard a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand. If you can’t, this attack does nothing.

name: Tapu Bulu
flavorText: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

attack.name: Wood Hammer
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Houndour
flavorText: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

name: Houndoom
flavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

attack.name: Snarl
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do 100 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Iron Moth
flavorText: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

attack.name: Suction
attack.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Anachronism Repulsor
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Ancient Pokémon.

name: Horsea
flavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

attack.name: Hold Still
attack.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Seadra
flavorText: It’s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

attack.name: Call for Backup
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Kingdra ex

attack.name: King’s Order
attack.text: Put up to 3 Water Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench.

attack.name: Hydro Pump
attack.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Sneasel
flavorText: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.

attack.name: Beset
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Weavile
flavorText: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.

attack.name: Hail Claw
attack.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
· Tera Pokémon ex rule: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent’s).
name: Revavroom ex

attack.name: Accelerator Flash
attack.text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

attack.name: Shattering Speed
attack.text: Discard this Pokémon and all attached cards.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.

attack.name: Eerie Gaze
attack.text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Hypno
flavorText: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

attack.name: Daydream
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, if they attach an Energy card from their hand to the Defending Pokémon, their turn ends.

name: Duskull
flavorText: Duskull’s victims suffer an intense chill as the Pokémon siphons their life-force away, glaring at them with its bright red eye all the while.

attack.name: Come and Get You
attack.text: Put up to 3 Duskull from your discard pile onto your Bench.

name: Dusclops

abilities.name: Cursed Blast
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put 5 damage counters on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. If you use this Ability, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.

flavorText: Dusclops’s true form is said to be a bright red eye burning within its body, but no one has ever seen such a thing.

name: Dusknoir

abilities.name: Cursed Blast
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put 13 damage counters on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. If you use this Ability, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.

flavorText: It comes and goes between this world and the afterlife. People fear this Pokémon because it is said to suck in lost spirits and take them along.

attack.name: Shadow Bind
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Cresselia
flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

attack.name: Healing Pirouette
attack.text: Heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attack.name: Crescent Purge
attack.text: You may turn 1 of your face-down Prize cards face up. If you do, this attack does 80 more damage. (That Prize card remains face up for the rest of the game.)

name: Sylveon
flavorText: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.

attack.name: Mystical Return
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. Shuffle that Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

attack.name: Disarming Voice
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.

attack.name: Frog Hop
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

attack.name: Clean Hit
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Bloodmoon Ursaluna

abilities.name: Battle-Hardened
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Basic {F} Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This special Ursaluna can see in the dark with its left eye and protects itself with mud that is as hard as iron.

attack.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.

attack.name: Mad Bite
attack.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Slither Wing
flavorText: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

attack.name: Iron Smasher
attack.text: If your opponent has any Future Pokémon in play, this attack does 120 more damage.

attack.name: Smashing Wing
attack.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Zubat
flavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

attack.name: Lead
attack.text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Golbat
flavorText: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

attack.name: Pitch-Black Blade
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

name: Crobat

abilities.name: Shadowy Envoy
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if you played Janine’s Secret Art from your hand this turn, you may draw cards until you have 8 cards in your hand.

flavorText: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.

attack.name: Poison Fang
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

name: Absol
flavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

attack.name: Darkfall
attack.text: If you have at least 3 Darkness Energy in play, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Zorua
flavorText: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

attack.name: Double Scratch
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Zoroark
flavorText: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

attack.name: Illusory Hijacking
attack.text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent’s Pokémon ex and Pokémon V in play.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

attack.name: Mischievous Tentacles
attack.text: Look at the top card of your opponent’s deck. You may have your opponent shuffle their deck.

name: Malamar
flavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar’s control.

attack.name: Colluding Tentacles
attack.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. If you do, this attack does 120 damage to the new Active Pokémon. If you didn’t play Xerosic’s Machinations from your hand during this turn, this attack does nothing.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

attack.name: Corrosive Winds
attack.text: Put 2 damage counters on each of your opponent’s Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

attack.name: Destructive Beam
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Okidogi ex

attack.name: Poisonous Musculature
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Darkness Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, this Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attack.name: Chain-Crazed
attack.text: If this Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 130 more damage.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Munkidori ex

abilities.name: Oh No You Don’t
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon, and if you have any Pecharunt ex in play, your opponent takes 1 fewer Prize card.

attack.name: Dirty Headbutt
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use Dirty Headbutt.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Fezandipiti ex

abilities.name: Flip the Script
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent’s last turn, you may draw 3 cards. You can’t use more than 1 Flip the Script Ability each turn.

attack.name: Cruel Arrow
attack.text: This attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Pecharunt ex

abilities.name: Subjugating Chains
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may switch 1 of your Benched {D} Pokémon, except any Pecharunt ex, with your Active Pokémon. If you do, the new Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. You can’t use more than 1 Subjugating Chains Ability each turn.

attack.text: Once during your turn, you may switch 1 of your Benched Darkness Pokémon, except any Pecharunt ex, with your Active Pokémon. If you do, the new Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. You can’t use more than 1 Subjugating Chains Ability each turn.

attack.name: Irritated Outburst
attack.text: This attack does 60 damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Genesect

abilities.name: ACE Nullifier
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, your opponent can’t play any ACE SPEC cards from their hand.

flavorText: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

name: Cufant
flavorText: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.

name: Copperajah

abilities.name: Massive Body
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can’t play any Stadium cards from their hand.

flavorText: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.

attack.name: Nasal Lariat
attack.text: You may do 100 more damage. If you do, during your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

name: Varoom
flavorText: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.

attack.name: Rigidify
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Axew
flavorText: If you see peculiar teeth marks on boulders or trees, it means an Axew is likely living nearby.

name: Fraxure

abilities.name: Unnerve
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent plays an Item or Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Fraxure uses its thick tusks to neatly cut prey into two portions—one to eat now and one to save for later.

attack.name: Dragon Pulse
attack.text: Discard the top card of your deck.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: It overwhelms enemies with its prized tusks, which are sharp enough to cut through a metal transmission tower in one strike.

attack.name: Bring Down the Axe
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, it is Knocked Out.

attack.name: Dragon Pulse
attack.text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

name: Kyurem

abilities.name: Plasma Bane
abilities.text: If your opponent has any cards in their discard pile that have “Colress” in the name, this Pokémon can use the Trifrost attack for {C}.

flavorText: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.

attack.text: If your opponent has any cards in their discard pile that have “Colress” in the name, this Pokémon can use the Trifrost attack for Colorless.

attack.name: Trifrost
attack.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 110 damage to 3 of your opponent’s Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Meowth
flavorText: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.

attack.name: Fury Swipes
attack.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Persian
flavorText: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.

attack.name: Fury Swipes
attack.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Eevee
flavorText: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.

attack.name: Colorful Catch
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Energy cards of different types, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Furfrou
flavorText: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

attack.name: Energy Assist
attack.text: Attach a Basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Stufful
flavorText: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

attack.name: Take Down
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Bewear
flavorText: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

attack.name: Power Charger
attack.text: Search your deck for a Basic Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Stadium rule: You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can’t be played.
name: Academy at Night

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Once during each player’s turn, that player may put a card from their hand on top of their deck.

rules: · Pokémon Tool rule: You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
name: Binding Mochi

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Attacks used by the Poisoned Pokémon this card is attached to do 40 more damage to your opponent’s Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Cassiopeia

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: You can use this card only when it is the last card in your hand. Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Colress’s Tenacity

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card and an Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Dangerous Laser

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Janine’s Secret Art

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Choose up to 2 of your Darkness Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a Basic Darkness Energy card and attach it to that Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you attached Energy to your Active Pokémon in this way, it is now Poisoned.

rules: · ACE SPEC rule: You can’t have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.

name: Neutralization Zone

abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to Pokémon that don’t have a Rule Box (both yours and your opponent’s) by attacks from the opponent’s Pokémon ex and Pokémon V. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.) This card can’t be put into your hand or deck from the discard pile.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Night Stretcher

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Put a Pokémon or a Basic Energy card from your discard pile into your hand.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
· ACE SPEC rule: You can’t have more than 1 ACE SPEC card in your deck.
name: Poké Vital A

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Heal 150 damage from 1 of your Pokémon. This card can’t be put into your hand or deck from the discard pile.

rules: · Pokémon Tool rule: You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
name: Powerglass

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: At the end of your turn (after your attack), if the Pokémon this card is attached to is in the Active Spot, you may attach a Basic Energy card from your discard pile to it.

attack.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon has any Darkness Energy attached, you may move up to 3 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon.

attack.name: Mind Bend
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Fezandipiti

abilities.name: Adrena-Pheromone
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any {D} Energy attached and is damaged by an attack, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

name: Okidogi

abilities.name: Adrena-Power

flavorText: Okidogi is a ruffian with a short temper. It can pulverize anything by swinging around the chain on its neck.
